  "prompt": "Is it a myth that consuming curd at dinner is bad for your health?",
  "response": "The idea that consuming curd at dinner is bad for your health is more of a traditional belief rather than a scientifically proven fact. In many cultures, it is suggested that eating curd at night can cause respiratory issues or digestive problems. However, there is no substantial scientific evidence to categorically support this claim.\n\nCurd (or yogurt) is a source of probiotics, calcium, protein, and other nutrients, and generally can be part of a healthy diet. Some people might experience digestive discomfort due to lactose intolerance or individual sensitivities, which could be more pronounced at night, but this varies from person to person.\n\nIt's always recommended to listen to your body and observe how it reacts to different foods at different times. Consulting with a healthcare provider or a nutritionist can help you determine what works best for your specific health needs.",
